reviews_data.review_text:
When I stepped into Bitty & Beaus's.I knew I'd found something special. The atmosphere was instantly welcoming, a perfect blend of cozy and vibrant. The decor created a comfortable space, ideal for both catching up with friends and getting some work done.

The service was exceptional. The baristas were welcoming, knowledgeable, and extremely hard working to provide quick orders!

The coffee was absolutely delicious! It's clear they use high-quality beans and take pride in their craft.

The music selection was spot-on, creating a relaxed and enjoyable backdrop without being overpowering. It complemented the overall ambiance perfectly.

What truly sets Bitty & Beau's apart is the people. The other patrons were friendly, and there was a real sense of community. It felt like a place where everyone was welcome.

In short, Bitty and Beau's has nailed it. With its exceptional service, inviting atmosphere, great music, friendly people, and, of course, fantastic coffee, it's quickly become my new go-to spot on Saturday morninga. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a truly enjoyable coffee shop experience.

I sensed home immediately when entered the place. Written from a deaf perspective, I fit in this place instantly after interacting with neurodivergent workers. Empathy and safe space were felt in the room. When ordered, I found out that one of the workers knew ASL which was a nice surprise. The playing card game method for awaiting pickups was innovative. It was visual “call out” rather than audible method which is known as ‘universal design’. What a genius idea. Worth my experience. And it will be worth yours too as well. This place will deepen your appreciation and your perspective will be broadened.

Aside from the unique coffee shop, parking can be problematic for some. The difficulty of finding free parking will depend on time and days which is not uncommon.

Has potential due to the nice atmosphere and location but needs real baristas and actual espresso machines.  Not the same machines that you basically see in airline lounges that are self serve.

Was in town on a work trip and stopped by with a group.  I asked for a cortado or espresso macchiato. The cashier looked confused and after a moment told me they only have "push button machines" and can't make one.

Fine.....I'll do it myself I thought.  I ordered a small cappuccino, planned to just pour the excess milk out and when I opened the lid to the drink, it was so full of milk that it made a mess all over the cup due to being filled all the way to the top.

Even after pouring out half of the cup the drink was still not good at all.  Just tasted like hot milk with with a hint of coffee.

So overall,  if you aren't into pre-made drinks from a push button machine consider another establishment.  I can't say I would return.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for visiting and sharing your feedback. We're sorry to hear about your experience. Our high-quality espresso machines are used by many leaders in the coffee space. However, a cortado is not a standard menu item and may have caught our new team member off guard. We employ individuals with disabilities who are continuously learning and growing. We appreciate your input and will address these concerns.

Regarding a refund, our apologies. We're not sure if you are aware that our shop is run by a staff with disabilities (this explains the phrase “more than a cup of coffee”).  We don’t think the person working the register communicated your request for a refund to the team lead, as he was trying to understand what had happened.  Regardless, we have searched the transactions and issued a refund this evening. Please allow 2-3 business days to see this come through.
